title: Lion_Start
---
A lion strides from the thicket, head high and mane bristling. It will not yield the road — its hunger is for your fear.
<<fight_start>>
===


title: Lion_RoarBack
---
You square your shoulders and roar back, daring it to come.
The lion answers with a charge that shakes the ground.
<<fight_dodge "lion_charge">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    Pride met with pride only makes it prouder. The lion paws the earth, ready for more.
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===


title: Lion_StandTall
---
You hold your ground and refuse to look away.
The lion takes the challenge and presses you hard.
<<fight_dodge "lion_roar">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    Standing firm keeps you alive — but a locked gaze is still a challenge to a proud beast.
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===


title: Lion_ShowHumility
---
You lower your eyes, bow your head, and make yourself no threat at all.
<<fight_dodge "lion_roar">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    With no pride to push against, the lion's fury has nowhere to go. Its roar softens to a low, watchful rumble.
    <<fight_spare_enable>>
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===


title: Lion_Win
---
The lion regards you a long moment, then turns aside with regal grace and lets you pass.
===


title: Lion_Lose
---
The lion's pride is a mountain you cannot climb. It overwhelms you, and the road is lost.
===
